question.text: In the IVF technique, which of the following is transferred into the fallopian tube?

options.text: Either  <math><mfenced separators="|"><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mfenced separators="|"><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">B</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>

solution.text: In vitro fertilization is the fertilization outside the body in similar conditions as that in the body is the method which sperm from the male and ovum from the female are collected and are induced to form zygote or in early embryo with up to 8 blastomeres could then be transferred into a fallopian tube.
